goals.question: What is the correlation between CO2 levels and adjusted CO2 levels?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('CO2')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of CO2 levels over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'], label='CO2')
    ax.plot(data['Date'], data['adjusted_CO2'], label='Adjusted CO2')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('CO2 Levels')
    ax.set_title('What is the difference between CO2 and adjusted CO2 levels?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['CO2'], bins=50, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean CO2: {:.2f}'.format(data['CO2'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median CO2: {:.2f}'.format(data['CO2'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Levels')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 levels?')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.strftime('%Y')
    data = data.groupby('Year').mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['Year'], data['CO2'], color='green')
    ax.axhline(y=data['CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average CO2 level')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('CO2 level')
    ax.set_title('What is the average CO2 level per year?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['CO2'], data['adjusted_CO2'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['CO2'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='CO2 mean')
    ax.axhline(y=data['adjusted_CO2'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label='adjusted_CO2 mean')
    ax.set_xlabel('CO2')
    ax.set_ylabel('adjusted_CO2')
    ax.set_title('What is the correlation between CO2 levels and adjusted CO2 levels?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
